            depositor;

guaranteed investment certificates, not to exceed 3 years, issued by a savings
            institution and registered in the name of the minister, the interest from which may be
            payable to the person who takes out the certificate;

irrevocable letters of credit, issued by a savings institution, with a
            termination date beyond the required term of security and containing a promise to pay
            the minister a specified sum on written demand;

